abstract: Rising cost of gasoline helps push up the price index, but the pressure is expected to ease in the months ahead; Labor Dept reports it rose 0.3 percent in September compared with 0.4 percent rise in August.
snippet: The rising cost of gasoline helped push up the price index, but the pressure is expected to ease in the months ahead.
lead_paragraph: The rising cost of gasoline helped push up the price index, but the pressure is expected to ease in the months ahead.

headline.main: Food and Gasoline Helped Push the Consumer Price Index Higher in September

headline.seo: Food and Gasoline Drove Consumer Prices Higher in September
